==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Triviality
<hw>Triv`i*al"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Trivialities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>trivialit⟦eacute⟧</ets>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or
state of being trivial; trivialness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is trivial; a trifle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The philosophy of our times does not expend itself in furious
discussions on mere scholastic <qex>trivialities</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Lyon Playfair.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trivially</ent>⟦br⟧
